post_text:
FAYETTE FALL SPORTS PLAN:

Fayette sports WILL be taking place this Fall, however, things will look different than normal. Please read the Fall Sports Plan, which has been approved by the Fulton Co Health Department, to know what to expect.

The biggest changes to note:

*ALL spectators must wear face masks and socially distance in the crowds at all times.
*Each volleyball player may invite up to 4 family members to come to the games as spectators.
*No one is permitted to enter Volleyball games unless they have a voucher that allows them to purchase a ticket (they will receive these from the volleyball player they are there to watch).
*Visiting volleyball players will be limited to 2 spectators per player.
*Doors for volleyball games will not open until 20 minutes before game time.
*There will not be concessions sold at volleyball games.

As Fayette is moving closer to the opening of school, Fayette needs some information from parents/guardians.

Go to the Fayette Website (https://www.fayettesch.org/default.aspx)

If you are planning on sending your student to the school building we need some information from you on transportation to school. Please fill out the Transportation Form.

If you are interested in having your student/s attend Fayette Virtual Academy, an informational document Fayette Online Information is available. If you wish to enroll your student/s to attend online please fill out the 2020-2021 Online Enrollment Form. The deadline for registering for Fayette Virtual Academy is August 11, 2020.

If you have any questions please contact Mrs. Reucher, Elementary Principal, Mr. Molter, JH/HS Principal or Dr. Belcher, Superintendent.

We are excited to announce that the Fayette Local School District has partnered with FinalForms, an online forms and data management service. FinalForms will be used to streamline all paperwork for registration as well as with athletics. FinalForms saves data from season-to-season and year-to-year, meaning that you will never need to enter the same information twice!

You may review your data at any time to verify it is current. You will be required to sign your forms once per year and after any update.

Thank you for your assistance!
Angie Belcher, Ed.D
Superintendent

shared_text:
State FFA Degrees | 2020 Ohio FFA Celebration

Ohio FFA premiered a video.
May 7 at 6:47 PM ·

FRIDAY, MAY 8 - 12:00pm | STATE FFA DEGREES

This year, 956 Ohio FFA members earned their State FFA Degree, the highest honor a state can bestow upon its members.

These individuals exemplify hard work, passion and an incredible level of dedication. These members have remained committed to their Supervised Agricultural Experiences as well as their involvement in their FFA Chapters and communities.

Congratulations to all of Ohio’s 2020 State FFA Degree recipients!

Thank you for supporting these awards, Farm Credit Mid-America!

#CelebrateOHFFA

shared_text:
Proficiency Awards | 2020 Ohio FFA Celebration

Ohio FFA premiered a video.
May 4 at 2:58 PM ·

TUESDAY, MAY 5 - 4:00pm | PROFICIENCY AWARDS

Hard work, passion and time are just a few qualities that it takes to climb to the top. These individuals spent many hours working hard on their Supervised Agricultural Experiences that they have a passion for. Whether it’s livestock, crops or agricultural communication, we are about to see the top individuals of each proficiency area. Thorough record keeping, research, labor and more have led these finalists to success. Thank you to all the businesses, organizations, individuals and families for making these awards possible.

The winner of each category will represent Ohio nationally later this year. Congratulations to all proficiency finalists and winners!

post_text:
Elementary Parents:
Classes resume via distance learning this upcoming Monday, April 6th. If you have not already, please make sure you are checking your Dojo messages for updates from your teachers. All kindergarten through sixth grade classes are organized through Google Classroom. Your child's teacher has invited you to join their class on Google Classroom, so if you have not already, take a minute to have your student join their class. You will find their weekly schedule within their classroom. Our specials classes have created one Classroom as well, which will include one weekly activity to continue to engage our students in each special area as well!
Do not hesitate to contact me via Dojo, e-mail areucher@fayettesch.org, or phone 419-237-2776 ext. 1010 with any questions!

post_text: This year’s Right to Read Week was a March Madness theme! The staff participated in a basketball game to kick-off the fun. The entire elementary is completing a reading bracket challenge to pick our favorite book by the end of March. Today students that turned in their reading BINGO cards got to shoot one basket. 10 baskets=one staff member getting ice dumped on them! Mrs. Reucher lucked out and ended up with confetti! We love reading at Fayette Elementary!

shared_text:
Fayette Police Department
November 11, 2019 at 2:39 PM ·

Urgent message to parents of Fayette Local School children.

We will be continuing classes as normal during the power outage. All children and staff are safe and we have generator backup for limited power. The school has water and is still warm.

All extracurricular activities for tonight including the FFA Leadership Conference have been cancelled.

It is unknown how long this outage will last.

We will dismiss at the end of the day as normal

Be safe, road conditions are worsening.

shared_text:
Fayette Police Department
July 28, 2019 at 11:09 AM ·

Fayette Bull Thistle Fireworks Info!

See the map below for parking and seating information at the Fireworks Show at the Fayette Local Schools on Saturday night, August 3rd, at dusk.

We welcome you to view the fireworks on the new ball diamonds and soccer fields, the east parking lot, the west side of the building, the front grassy area and other spots around the school properties.

If you live in town it would be best to walk to the school.

Parking will be in the main lots and the new fields lots.
HANDICAP PARKING WILL BE ALONG THE EAST SCHOOL DRIVE NEAR THE BALL FIELDS.

When leaving, please follow police officers directions as traffic will be routed based on your parking location.

The best viewing will be on the back school parking lot and for families coming early, throw a blanket down on the west side of the building in the grassy area and the kids can play on the playground.

Please be careful and be safe. All dogs must be on a leash and if they are afraid of fireworks, please leave them at home. No alcoholic beverages allowed.
